The All Progressives Congress (APC) will on Saturday commenced it’s congresses in Rivers State.
The Congress is sequel to the recent court ruling setting the court injunction against the state congresses aside
In a statement from the APC National Organising Secretary, Chief Emma Ibediro, the Congress would start on Saturday and end the following day.
Ibediro, in the timetable released, said: “In line with the lifting of the restraining order on the Rivers State Congresses, the All Progressives Congress (APC) hereby notify our Party Members and the General Public that our Party has rescheduled to hold Congresses in the state.”